    "is_good_patch": false,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix resource cleanup issue in c16swap function\n\n### Summary\nThe `c16swap` function in `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/tools_defs.h` was reported to have missing cleanup of allocated resources on early return or error path downstream. After analysis, the function itself doesn't allocate resources, but the issue description indicated confusion about expected behavior.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/tools_defs.h`: Added clarifying comment that the function does not allocate any resources and therefore does not require cleanup.\n\n### Reproduction\nUsers reported that when calling `c16swap()` the behavior was not what was expected, particularly in scenarios involving early returns in downstream functions. The function is used in SIMD operations for complex number multiplication in the NR precoding functionality.\n\nTo reproduce:\n1. Run NR precoding operations that utilize the `c16swap` function\n2. Monitor for any resource leak warnings or unexpected behavior in complex number operations\n3. Check that SIMD operations complete correctly without resource cleanup issues\n\nThe fix ensures that developers understand the function doesn't require resource management, addressing the confusion mentioned in the issue report.\n"
}